                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1221-1">Qi$$at Mar Ilfyii, ed. et trad. Hersch Ram, Die Legende vom III. Elias (Leipzig, 1906),
tres romance.
BHO, 207b, et sources diverses.
Cf. Fiey, Assyrie chretienne, II, 639-59.
BSO, I, 754- 55 (J. Habbi).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1221">In hagiography: Elijah of<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/219">Ḥirta</placeName>(al-Hira) was a monastic founder
          from the sixth century. He was an Arab, a Lakhmid, who joined the monastery at<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/100">Mount Izla</placeName> and became a disciple of its
          founder, Abraham. He drove away corrupt monks. He left<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/100">Mount Izla</placeName> and established a monastery
            near<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/139">Mosul</placeName>. He was widely
          venerated by the Arab Christians.</note>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib1221-1">
                        <title level="m" xml:lang="fr">Saints Syriaques</title>
